:: Lesson 32: Reconsider â€” coercing to a specific type in proofs

environ
 vocabularies XBOOLE_0, SUBSET_1;
 notations SUBSET_1;
 constructors SUBSET_1;

begin

theorem
  for X being set, x being object st x in X holds
  ex y being Element of X st y = x
proof
  let X be set, x be object;
  assume A1: x in X;
  reconsider y = x as Element of X by A1;
  take y; thus y = x;
end;
